  "total_chunks": 13,
  "chunks": [
    {
      "chunk_text": "This is a download from BBC Learning English.To find out more, visit our website.",
      "chunk_id": "f03ab006-7b7f-439a-ac62-bb796e3b268c",
      "chunk_index": 0,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176715",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Why are prices going up_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 81,
      "enhanced_tags": [],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.996246"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Yes, I have, Beth. It seems like consumers, like us, are being hit in the pocket at the moment. And by that, I mean we have less money to spend.",
      "chunk_id": "a4b822c7-ffd2-4669-8e81-6d0033516c6d",
      "chunk_index": 1,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176715",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Why are prices going up_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 144,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.998469"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Ok, we'll find out if you're right later on.",
      "chunk_id": "97857d04-89a5-4472-bff4-f324b4edf168",
      "chunk_index": 2,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176715",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Why are prices going up_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 44,
      "enhanced_tags": [],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:14.000563"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Two things in particular are increasing in price – energy, like gas and electricity, and food. These are things we need and depend on. So what's causing the rises?",
      "chunk_id": "a7c69c16-bb57-40c9-889f-3be051d5b5eb",
      "chunk_index": 3,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176715",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Why are prices going up_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 163,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "CI",
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:14.002956"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Even when things are in short supply, available in limited quantities, prices go up. The BBC World Service programme The Real Story discussed this in much more detail. One expert, economist, writer and broadcaster, Linda Yu, explained how price rises could be around for a while.",
      "chunk_id": "b55fc0f9-3e00-42f8-9641-e8d59a9d8119",
      "chunk_index": 4,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176715",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Why are prices going up_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 279,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "ROA",
        "XP",
        "ES",
        "AI"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:14.005343"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Linda Yu used some interesting language there. She talked about food and energy being volatile items.",
      "chunk_id": "72f3ef50-f4c7-496a-bd5b-80062c629d50",
      "chunk_index": 5,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176715",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Why are prices going up_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 101,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:14.007479"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Yes, and she said these price increases have been sustained, so continuing at the same level for a long period of time. But Linda Yu says that even if energy and food prices eventually come down, companies will pass on the extra costs they've already faced by charging more for their goods and services.",
      "chunk_id": "5bdc5fec-236d-4a19-bed8-36a5728bb334",
      "chunk_index": 6,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176715",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Why are prices going up_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 303,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "UI",
        "ES",
        "AI"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:14.009883"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Another possible consequence of inflation is recession. This economic term describes a situation where a country's production starts going down, people's incomes go down and unemployment goes up.",
      "chunk_id": "d0580295-a550-461e-a6fd-66642bf258f5",
      "chunk_index": 7,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176715",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Why are prices going up_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 195,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "Inflation",
        "軟實力",
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:14.012168"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "So what can be done? Well, that's the million dollar question and economists are trying to work it out. Speaking on The Real Story programme, economist Vicki Price gave an overview of how to control inflation.",
      "chunk_id": "51a1fade-4a11-417e-bf50-de2a6a3a499d",
      "chunk_index": 8,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176715",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Why are prices going up_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 209,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "Inflation",
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:14.014453"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "And if we borrow less money, we buy fewer things, which can reduce inflation. I think it makes sense now. And if you were in Venezuela in 2018, you would really want inflation to go down, wouldn't you?",
      "chunk_id": "5125b1aa-c1b3-4d3a-9e37-ee637d498a54",
      "chunk_index": 9,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176715",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Why are prices going up_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 201,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "Inflation",
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:14.017456"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "I asked you what one report said the inflation rate was there between November 2017 and 2018. And I said a very high 1,300%. Well, it was even higher, Beth. According to a study by the Opposition Controlled National Assembly, the annual inflation rate reached 1,300,000% in the 12 months to November 2018. This extreme financial situation was known as hyperinflation.",
      "chunk_id": "8f659fb0-e1d6-40bf-9f18-748e28711e78",
      "chunk_index": 10,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176715",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Why are prices going up_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 367,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "Inflation",
        "LED",
        "CI",
        "專業技能",
        "AI",
        "SEM"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:14.019989"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "In this programme, we have been talking about inflation. That's the increase in prices over time. Other vocabulary we used included the expression hit in the pocket, which means you have less money to spend.",
      "chunk_id": "365ad9e7-5e47-4ce3-822b-81c580420d0c",
      "chunk_index": 11,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176715",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Why are prices going up_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 207,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "Inflation",
        "XP",
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:14.022319"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "And interest rates are fees banks and financial institutions charge you for borrowing money. Well, we hope you found our brief lesson about the economy useful. Thanks for listening. Goodbye for now. Bye bye.",
      "chunk_id": "3c9303ef-d024-44e8-ac0b-1b8804c456b3",
